column15: Brazilian dairy breed created by crossing Gir and Holstein (3/8 Gir, 5/8 Holstein)
Hardy beef breed from Russia and Kazakhstan.
Local Romanian milk breed, the result of crossbreeding between Braunvieh and local Mocanita and Grey cattle.
Indigenous Iranian breed raised for meat, milk, and fiber (mohair).
Israeli sheep breed that is a product of crossbreeding Awassi and East Friesian; dual purpose milk and meat breed with white wool
One of the main sheep breeds in Egypt, well-adapted to the desert environment.
Hardy French breed characterized by brownish-black wool, prolificacy, and good milk production.
Czech breed originated from a native breed improved by crossing with German Brown bucks.
Australian meat sheep breed derived from selective breeding of White Dorper, Van Rooy, Poll Dorset, and Texel.
French sheep breed originating from the southern part of the Massif Central. Known for its hardiness and adaptibility to harsh conditions.
